HEADWORD: adoring
<hw>adoring</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fr>1</fr> <def>feeling or
showing profound respect or veneration. Opposite of
<ant>irreverent</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> worshipful, reverent</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fr>1</fr> <def>feeling or showing a deep love and
devotion to.</def> <illu>her <ex>adoring</ex> parents</illu>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> doting, fond, lovesome</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adoringly</ent>⟦br⟧
